               <msContents>
                  <summary>The Ms. contains only one text:&#xD; I) Maṣḥafa ʾAslǝṭi, Lectionary for
                     the entire year (fols. 5ra-67ra)&#xD; I-1) Scriptural readings for liturgical
                     periods, fasts and feasts for the entire year (fols. 5ra-67ra) &#xD; -
                     Liturgical period Yoḥannǝs: fols. 5ra-7va&#xD; - Feasts of the Martyrs
                     (Samāʿtāt): fols. 7va-8va&#xD; - Liturgical period Masqal: fols. 25va-27rb&#xD;
                     - Feasts of the Righteous Ones (Ṣādǝqān): fols. 10rb-11va&#xD; - Liturgical
                     period Ṣǝge: fols. 11va-13ra&#xD; - Feast of the stay of the Holy Family at
                     Mount Qosqam in Egypt and feast of Mary (Qʷǝsqʷām): fols. 13ra-16va&#xD; -
                     Feast of Archangel Michael (Qǝddus Mikāʾel): fols. 16va-18vb&#xD; - Feast of
                     the harvest (Maʿǝrar): fol. 18vb-19vb&#xD; - Liturgical period Sǝbkat: fols.
                     19vb-21rb&#xD; - Liturgical period Bǝrhan: fols. 21rb-22va&#xD; - Liturgical
                     period Nolāwi: fols. 22va-24ra&#xD; - Liturgical period Lǝdat: fols.
                     24ra-25va&#xD; - Feast of the Circumcision (Gǝzrat): fols. 25va-27ra&#xD; -
                     Feast of the Epiphany (Ṭǝmqat): fols. 27ra-29ra&#xD; - Feasts of the Righteous
                     Ones (Ṣādǝqān): fols. 29ra-30va&#xD; - Feast of Simeon, Presentation of the
                     Lord (Sǝmʿon): fols. 30va-34va&#xD; - Week of Nicodemus (Niqodimos) and feast
                     of the Archangel Gabriel (Qǝddus Gabrǝʾel): fols. 34va-36va&#xD; - Palm Sunday
                     (Hosāʿǝnā): fols. 36va-38rb&#xD; - Maundy Thursday (Ṣalota Ḫamus):
                     fols.38rb-43ra&#xD; - Vigil of Easter (maḫatǝwa Fāsikā): fols. 43ra-44va&#xD; -
                     Easter (Fāsikā): fols. 44va-47ra&#xD; - Sunday after Easter (ʾAgbǝʾota Gǝbǝr or
                     Faṣṣamna): fols. 47ra-48va&#xD; - Pentecost (Ṗanṭaqosṭe or Ṗārāqliṭos): fols.
                     48va-50rb&#xD; - Ascension (ʿƎrgat): fols. 50rb-51vb&#xD; - Pentecost
                     (Ṗārāqliṭos): fols. 51vb-54ra&#xD; - Liturgical period Kǝramt (“Rainy season”):
                     fols. 54ra-56rb&#xD; - Fast of the Apostles (Ḥawāryāt): fols. 56rb-57rb&#xD; -
                     Feasts of the Virgin (Dǝngǝl): fols. 57rb-59rb&#xD; - Transfiguration (Dabra
                     Tābor): fols. 59rb-61ra&#xD; - Feast of Abraham (ʾAbrǝham): fols.
                     61ra-62vb&#xD; I-2) Scriptural readings for Hours of Sunday (fols.
                     62vb-67ra)&#xD; &#xD; Additio 1</summary>
